CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 6, 1959, pg. 1 reads: "Removing Debris - With a bulldozer and other wrecking vehicles, a crew of workmen on Monday were removing the remains of the three-story building at 616 Protectory Pl., which collapsed last Friday evening. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Rubble from collapsed building being removed by bulldozer and dump truck, 616 Protector Place, Hill District
